Annotation: One document bears Evers' signature and stamp ("Prof. Fr. Hans Gerhard Evers 6101 Traisa bei Darmstadt Heldeweg 2 . Tel. 06151/14308")

Description:
Annotation on the envelope: "(Rubens) Rudloff 24.11.1976 Abrah[a?]m u [und?] Melchisedek (Maria m. Kind)".

  • Photocopies of a french catalogue about 'Abraham and Melchizedek'
  • Dated (24.11.1976) and signed (by Evers) sheets with comments about 'Abraham and Melchizedek' by Rubens.
  • A library loan record
  • Dr. Rudloff's business card
  • Report by Dr. G. Busch Kustos (Kunsthalle Bremen, 01.12.1948)
  • Copies of paintings
  • Records about 'Abraham and Melchizedek' paintings by Hans Witdoeck and Jacob Neefs

Loose documentation reunited with the folder:

  • Photograph of a painting of Abraham and Melchizedek.
